revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== From {{prefix|en|yester|season}}. ===Noun=== {{en-noun|-}} # A past or prior [[season]], last season; an earlier or [[previous]] [[period]] of time. #* '''2009''', Carlton Thurman, ''Caddie Esoterica'': #*: Dared try fly, we, these impassible trees, whose drive-capturing crests communicate failed shots to '''yesterseason's''' leafy cache [...] #* '''1980''', Vincent Gaston Dethier, ''The world of the tent-makers'': #*: The dried umbles of the Queen Anne's lace of '''yesterseason''', [...] ====Related terms==== * {{l|en|yestertide}}
